<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-10-04T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-10-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="193" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d193">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">837.61351/4353</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Cuba</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Braden</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 4686</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Habana</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-10-04">October 4, 1943</date>.<lb/>[Received October
                                9.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to previous correspondence
                            concerning Central Tinguaro, especially my despatch No. 4582 of
                            September 24, 1943<note n="18" xml:id="d193fn18">Not printed.</note>
                            transmitting a copy of my note to the Foreign Office<note n="19" xml:id="d193fn19">Note No. 1029, September 23, <ref target="#pg_205">p. 205</ref>.</note> in the premises, I have the honor to
                            enclose copy and translation of the reply,<note n="18" xml:id="d193fn20">Not printed.</note> which I have received from the Minister of
                            State.</p>
                        <p>This reply is merely an acknowledgment stating that the “matter is the
                            subject of the preferential attention of the pertinent
                                authorities…”<note n="20" xml:id="d193fn21">Omission indicated in
                                the original despatch.</note>
                            <pb facs="0223" n="209" xml:id="pg_209"/> and that “it will be a
                            pleasure” to inform me in due course of their decision.</p>
                        <p>Respectfully yours,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Spruille Braden</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>